Overview (important first)

	Steam on CRUX requires:

		Working X + OpenGL (already doing)
		32-bit compatibility layer
		32-bit NVIDIA OpenGL libs
		Steam port

If any one of those is missing, Steam will not start.

1) Enable 32-bit compatibility (once)

	Make sure compat-32 is enabled in /etc/prt-get.conf:

		###
		# compat-32
		###
		prtdir /usr/ports/compat-32


	Sync ports: prt-get update

2) Install core 32-bit runtime libs

	These are required before Steam itself.
		prt-get depinst glibc-32
		prt-get depinst gcc-libs-32
		prt-get depinst libstdc++-32

		(Yes, CRUX makes you be explicit.)

3) Install NVIDIA 32-bit OpenGL (mandatory)

	Since you’re using NVIDIA: prt-get install nvidia-32

		Without this:
			Steam starts
			Games crash or refuse to launch

4) Install Steam itself

	Steam lives in contrib (sometimes opt, depending on mirror).
		prt-get depinst steam (If it pulls deps, let it.)

5) First run (important)
	Run as normal user, inside X: steam

	First launch will:
		Download Steam runtime
		Update itself (Takes a few minutes, this is normal.)

6) Verify OpenGL (before installing games)

		In Steam: Help → System Information
		Check: OpenGL renderer → NVIDIA GTX 1650
		→ Not llvmpipe
		→ Not software rendering

		If wrong → 32-bit NVIDIA libs missing.

Common CRUX Steam failures (and fixes)
	❌ wrong ELF class
		→ missing glibc-32 or nvidia-32
	❌ Steam opens, games don’t
		→ nvidia-32 not installed
	❌ Black screen / crash
		→ X running on NVIDIA instead of Intel (PRIME misconfig)

Optional but recommended
	Install Vulkan (many games need it):
		prt-get depinst vulkan-loader
		prt-get depinst vulkan-loader-32

	Then:
		vulkaninfo | less

Minimal checklist

✔ X works
✔ nvidia-smi works
✔ nvidia-32 installed
✔ compat-32 enabled
✔ Steam port installed

When you’re back at the machine and done with X + NVIDIA, do not troubleshoot Steam until:
	glxinfo | grep OpenGL
		shows NVIDIA.
